Today, I‚Äôm continuing to meet with members of both parties to try and come up with a solution and I‚Äôm hopeful we can make sure our essential government services across our country are up and running while we continue policy debates in Washington.
They don‚Äôt actually disagree with anything in the funding bill, but are holding it hostage and demanding that Congress pass totally unrelated immigration legislation.
On Friday, Senate Democrats blocked that bipartisan funding bill using the power of the filibuster and refused to vote for anything at all unless their immigration policy demands are met.
The bill also reauthorized the Children‚Äôs Heath Insurance Program that ensures tens of thousands of low-income Kansas children have the care they need.
On Thursday, the House passed a bipartisan funding bill to keep our government running and continue to pay our troops, care for our vets, and provide Social Security benefits to our seniors.
...plus provide a much-needed long term extension for CHIP, as we continue to negotiate an immigration solution.

As I engage in conversations with other Members tonight, I‚Äôm hopeful that cooler heads will prevail and we will continue to do things like provide health care for our veterans, paychecks for our troops, and social security benefits for our seniors...
While immigration reform is certain an important priority, I do not believe shutting down the government is the right approach.

Email Privacy Act has 300 cosponsors in the House - a veto-proof super majority. But hasn't seen a hearing in committee yet. #ECPA29 (6/7)
Our digital communications, which are far more common in our 2015 world, deserve same protections as our paper communications. #ECPA29 (5/7)
.@RepJaredPolis and I have introduced the Email Privacy Act (HR 699) to bring our 4th Amendment rights into the 21st Century. #ECPA29 (4/7)
ECPA allows federal agencies to access any of your digital communications older than six months WITHOUT a warrant. #ECPA29 (3/7)
That's right, President Reagan signed ECPA into law 29 years ago today - and it's still governing our digital privacy rights. #ECPA29 (2/7)
In addition to it being #BackToTheFuture Day, today happens to be the Electronic Communications Privacy Act's 29th Birthday. #ECPA29 (1/7)
